text: Local old style western food, bbq, fried chicken. Affordable Western food for all, not much frills or sides.

Grumpy stakeholder, uninspiring signboard and high prices - but the food is surprisingly good.

I fact, best of its kind in ulu ulu Teban. If you are lucky to see barbequed chicken wings grab it. Forget the pastas or fried rice.  Fish and chips ($8) is okay but they should be more generous with the baked beans and coleslaw).

Personally I feel that our local guys should be given some support.
